    "recap_url": "https://www.gojacks.com/news/2026/3/21/baseball-jacks-sweep-doubleheader-win-home-series",
    "recap_headline": "South Dakota State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "South Dakota State scored in 11 of the 16 innings it batted and recorded 13 extra-base hits in sweeping a college baseball doubleheader from North Dakota State Saturday at Erv Huether Field.\nBy winning the opener, 13-5, and posting an 11-1, eight-inning victory in Game 2, the Jackrabbits improved to 7-17 overall and 2-4 in The Summit League. NDSU dropped to 4-19 overall and 1-5 in league play.\nGame 1: SDSU 13, NDSU 5\nLuke Luskey\nhomered twice, doubled and drove in five runs to lead the Jackrabbits to victory in the opener, ending a nine-game losing streak.\nTied at 3-all entering the bottom of the fourth, SDSU scored three times to take the lead for good.\nKeagen Jirschele\nled off the inning by advancing all the way to third base on a throwing error and scored the go-ahead run on an infield single by\nNolan Grawe\n. Two batters later, Luskey doubled to the right-center gap to plate\nNic Werk\n, and Luskey later scored on a base hit by\nNate Wachter\nto give the Jackrabbits a 6-3 lead.\nSDSU scored four more times against the Bison bullpen in the home half of the fifth. Jirschele again started the rally by being hit by a pitch and\nOwen Siegert\nand Grawe followed with back-to-back triples. A Werk sacrifice fly plated Grawe before Luskey connected on a solo homer to right-center.\nThe Bison cut the deficit to 10-5 with a pair of runs in the top of the sixth, but Luskey put the game out of reach with a three-run homer to left-center in the bottom of the seventh.\nSDSU tallied single runs in each of the first three innings, but trailed 3-2 after NDSU's Kyle Law hit a two-run inside-the-park home run in the top of the third.\nCarter Taylor's\nRBI double in the bottom of the third tied the game for the final time.\nJackrabbit starter\nSam Schlecht\nworked 4 1/3 innings before giving way to\nLogan Campbell\n. Schlecht struck out five and surrendered three runs \u2014 two earned \u2014 on eight hits in finishing with a no-decision.\nTristan Augedahl\nadded four strikeouts in 3 2/3 hitless and scoreless innings to earn the save.\nSDSU finished with a season-high 15 hits, six of which went for extra bases. Grawe, Luskey and Wachter each notched three hits.\nNoah Gordon and Bennett Freiter each tallied two of NDSU's nine hits.\nGame 2: SDSU 11, NDSU 1 (8 inn.)\nSam Novotny\npitched 7 2/3 strong innings and the Jackrabbits again scored runs in bunches to finish off the sweep of the twinbill.\nLuskey opened the scoring with his fourth extra-base of the day, lacing a double to the right-center gap in the bottom of the first inning to bring home\nOwen Siegert\n. An inning later, Jirschele led off with a double and scored on a sacrifice fly by\nLuke Wroblewski\n.\nThe Jackrabbit lead grew to 5-0 in the fourth when Grawe greeted reliever Zak Szabo with a double into the right-field corner that drove in both Wroblewski and Siegert. Grawe later scored on a steal of home.\nSDSU tacked on two more runs in the home half of the fifth on a two-run single by Siegert.\nThat was more than enough run support for Novotny, who took a shutout into the seventh. The only blemish on his record was a solo home run by Evan Gustafson with one out in the seventh as the Jackrabbit right-hander struck out a season-high nine batters. He left with the bases loaded in the top of the eighth, but reliever\nAustin Henry\nneeded only one pitch to get out of the jam by inducing a flyout to right field.\nThe Jackrabbits put the 10-run rule into effect in the bottom of the eighth with another four-run frame. Siegert and Grawe started the rally with their third hits of the game and Luskey walked to load the bases.\nDayton Franke\nthen bounced a single through the right side to score two and Jirschele ended the game with his third hit and second double of the contest to plate two more.\nSDSU out-hit NDSU, 12-5. Caleb Corbin posted two hits for the Bison.\nON DECK\nThe Jackrabbits open a four-game road trip Wednesday night with a matchup at Creighton. First pitch is slated for 6 p.m. at Charles Schwab Field in downtown Omaha, Nebraska.\nNOTES\nSDSU leads the all-time series, 136-89, but SDSU holds a 45-44 edge in Summit League regular season games since both programs joined the conference in 2008\nThe Jackrabbits' 13 extra-base hits in the doubleheader were nine doubles, two triples and two home runs, which produced a .697 slugging percentage on the day\nSDSU's six doubles in Game 2 were a season high\nLuskey recorded the fourth multi-home run game of his career and upped his career home run total to 26\nLuskey's run-scoring double in Game 2 produced his 100\nth\ncareer RBI in 108 games as a Jackrabbit\nJirschele scored six times in the doubleheader, including four times in the opener\nGrawe went 9-for-14 at the plate in the series with three hits in each of the three games\nNovotny's nine strikeouts were the most by a Jackrabbit pitcher this season\nJackrabbit pitchers combined for 30 strikeouts compared to nine walks in the three-game series\n-GoJacks.com-",
